    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-09-26T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-09-26T19:00:00-05:00" n="234"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d234">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/2335: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Acting Chairman of the American Delegation to the General Disarmament
                        Conference (<persName type="to">Gibson</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-09-26T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >September 26, 1932—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5. For <persName corresp="#p_WHR1">Wilson</persName>. Neutrals on 22nd proposed
                    to Bolivia and Paraguay<note n="14" xml:id="d234fn14">See <ref target="#pg_93"
                            >p. 93</ref>.</note> immediate cessation of hostilities without
                    conditions and submission of matter to arbitration without reservations. Bolivia
                    has accepted immediate cessation of hostilities but has not yet answered on
                    arbitration. Paraguay has accepted arbitration and immediate cessation of
                    hostilities but on condition that troops of both countries are withdrawn. Both
                    countries have accepted the sending of neutral delegation which will supervise
                    the maintenance of peace.</p>
                <p>Neutrals today pointed out to Paraguay that question of withdrawal of troops is a
                    matter which the Neutral Commission can take up as soon as hostilities are
                    terminated and is endeavoring in view thereof to have Paraguay accept proposal
                    of 22nd. Neutrals are trying to have Bolivia accept on point of arbitration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
